==Dutch==
[[Category:Dutch personal pronouns]]
[[Category:Dutch possessive pronouns]]
[[Category:Dutch reflexive pronouns]]
===Personal pronoun===
'''je'''

# ''Second-person singular, subjective, mute form:'' [[you]].
#: ''Wat doe je daar?'' &mdash; What are you doing there?
# ''Second-person singular, objective, mute form:'' [[you]].
#: ''Ik doe dit wel voor je.'' &mdash; I'll do this for you.
# ''Second-person plural, subjective, mute form:'' [[you]] (''plural'').
#: ''Wat doe je daar?'' &mdash; What are you doing there?
# ''Second-person plural, objective, mute form:'' [[you]] (''plural'').
#: ''Ik doe dit wel voor je.'' &mdash; I'll do this for you.

====Related terms====
: ''See [[Wiktionary:Dutch inflection#Pronouns|Wiktionary:Dutch inflection]]''

===Possessive pronoun===
'''je'''

# ''Second-person singular, mute form:'' [[your]].
#: ''Neem je boek en maak die oefening.'' &mdash; Take your book and make that exercise.
# ''Second-person plural, mute form:'' [[your]] (''plural'').
#: ''Neem je boek en maak die oefening.'' &mdash; Take your book and make that exercise.

====Related terms====
: ''See [[Wiktionary:Dutch inflection#Pronouns|Wiktionary:Dutch inflection]]''

===Reflexive pronoun===
'''je'''

# ''Second-person singular:'' [[yourself]].
#: ''Heb je je gewassen?'' &mdash; Did you wash yourself?
# ''Second-person plural:'' [[yourselves]].
#: ''Hebben jullie je goed voorbereid?'' &mdash; Have you all prepared yourselves well?

====Related terms====
: ''See [[Wiktionary:Dutch inflection#Pronouns|Wiktionary:Dutch inflection]]''

